The paper deals with the problem of errors in operational spreadsheets, which is a common issue in software engineering (cs.SE). The study also involves analyzing the impact of errors on the spreadsheet, which could fall under programming languages (cs.PL) and cybernetics (cs.CY). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential financial consequences of spreadsheet errors, which could relate to cryptography and security (cs.CR) and databases (cs.DB).
